Sentencas: (Pr0.9La0.1)(2)Ni0.74Cu0.21Ga0.05O4+delta (PLNCG) has been investigated as a potential cathode material based on Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-delta (CGO) electrolyte for intermediate-temperature solid-oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFC).
Titulo: (Pr0.9La0.1)2(Ni0.74Cu0.21Ga0.05)O4+δ as cathode material for CeO2-based intermediate-temperature solid-oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: X-ray diffraction analysis reveals that PLNCG powders with K2NiF4-type structure can be obtained from calcining the precursors at 950 degrees C for 10 h in air.
Titulo: (Pr0.9La0.1)2(Ni0.74Cu0.21Ga0.05)O4+δ as cathode material for CeO2-based intermediate-temperature solid-oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) value of PLNCG is 12.45 x 10(-6) K-1, which is extremely close to that of CGO (12.39 x 10(-6) K-1).
Titulo: (Pr0.9La0.1)2(Ni0.74Cu0.21Ga0.05)O4+δ as cathode material for CeO2-based intermediate-temperature solid-oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The PLNCG material exhibits a semiconductor-to-metal transition around 400 degrees C.
Titulo: (Pr0.9La0.1)2(Ni0.74Cu0.21Ga0.05)O4+δ as cathode material for CeO2-based intermediate-temperature solid-oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The value of area specific resistance (ASR) is 0.249, 0.118, 0.063 and 0.037 Omega cm(2) at 650, 700, 750, 800 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: (Pr0.9La0.1)2(Ni0.74Cu0.21Ga0.05)O4+δ as cathode material for CeO2-based intermediate-temperature solid-oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The CGO electrolyte-supported fuel cell is prepared using PLNCG as cathode and NiO-CGO (65:35 by weight) as anode.
Titulo: (Pr0.9La0.1)2(Ni0.74Cu0.21Ga0.05)O4+δ as cathode material for CeO2-based intermediate-temperature solid-oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The maximum power densities of the single-cell reach 407, 266 and 201 mW cm(-2) at 800, 750, and 700 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: (Pr0.9La0.1)2(Ni0.74Cu0.21Ga0.05)O4+δ as cathode material for CeO2-based intermediate-temperature solid-oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: These results indicate that the PLNCG can be a good candidate for cathode materials of IT-SOFC based on CGO electrolyte.
Titulo: (Pr0.9La0.1)2(Ni0.74Cu0.21Ga0.05)O4+δ as cathode material for CeO2-based intermediate-temperature solid-oxide fuel cell
